v0.0.16
candidates.body:
- Add Viewer for image show
- Update `MinOptMax` struct
- Add `.with_ixx` to simplify model building with `Options`

- Added `Hub` for resource management
- Updated `DataLoader` to support video and streaming
- Updated `CI.yaml`
- Replaced `println!` with `tracing` for logging

candidates.title: Fix the bug related to RGBA handling when resizing images
Accelerate model pre-processing and post-processing
candidates.body:
#### Updates:
- Add X struct to handle input and preprocessing.
- Add Ops struct to manage common operations.
- Use SIMD (`fast_image_resize`) to accelerate model pre-processing and post-processing. The models include: YOLO series, DB, ModNet, Depth-Anything, etc., with a speed increase of 75%-90%. For example, on my machine, YOLOv8m-seg post-processing decreased from 120ms to 20ms; Depth-Anything decreased from 23ms to only 2.1ms.
